A KwaZulu-Natal man suffered severe burns in a gas explosion at a home in Shaka's Rock on the north coast. An IPSS Medical Rescue team was dispatched on Monday  after a report of the explosion. “On arrival paramedics were met with an explosion scene that resulted in a male sustaining significant burns to his body. “Paramedics worked to stabilise the man while requesting aeromedical support.” The man was airlifted to St Augustine's hospital in Durban. TimesLIVE